==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jacquerie
<hw>Jacque`rie"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>The name given to a revolt of French peasants against the nobles in
1358, the leader assuming the contemptuous title, <etsep>Jacques
Bonhomme</etsep>, given by the nobles to the peasantry. Hence, any
revolt of peasants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jactancy</ent>⟦br⟧
